LVMH has no comment on GrandMet remarks . LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton declined on Thursday to comment on remarks by Grand Metropolitan ' s chief executive that a three - way drinks deal could be reached this year if benefits are fairly shared . A spokeswoman for the French group said LVMH was waiting for a reply from Guinness and GrandMet on chairman Bernard Arnault ' s proposal to create an independent , listed company blending the three companies ' wine and spirits businesses . " We are waiting for the final answer from Guinness and GrandMet , " the spokeswoman said . GrandMet chief executive John McGrath was quoted in the Financial Times as saying that any new deal " must demonstrate " that Guinness and GrandMet shareholders would benefit . 
